Sheet1.caption: Fried Korean tempeh tacos, with gochujang chile paste and radish kimchi, served in soft tortillas. The V Street restaurant's nutty tempeh and flavorful tofu prove chef-owner Rich Landau's mastery of meat-replacement.  (2015)

Sheet1.name: Fox & Son Fancy Corndogs

Sheet1.name: Fox & Son Fancy Corndogs
Sheet1.caption: Gluten-free corndogs at Fox & Son Fancy Corndogs in Reading Terminal Market. In order of appearance: chili cheese corndog;  corndog with ketchup and mustard; sweet potato battered corndog topped with cilantro sour cream, and chorizo; and the cheddar jalapeño corndog. Diners can choose among hot dogs including all beef, beef & pork, spicy pork, turkey and vegan.

Sheet1.name: Bareburger
Sheet1.caption: The Duchess, featured on Bareburger's extensive vegan menu, is one of their most popular vegan dishes. It includes the famous Impossible burger patty, garlic aioli, caramelized onions, melty 'Gouda,' baby kale and a tomato slice on a vegan 'Vrioche' bun.

Sheet1.name: Bareburger
Sheet1.caption: The crispy Brussels sprouts are a well-loved dish on Bareburger's vegan menu. They come fried with vegan Parmesan cheese -- a rare find -- as well as with lemon.
